## 1) Objective
Create a repeatable, auditable workflow for turning every patch/upgrade note into:
1. a scoped implementation plan,
2. code/config/docs changes,
3. verification evidence,
4. release-ready deliverables.

---

## 2) Required Output Format for `Patches&Upgrades`
To ensure full implementation coverage, each requested change should follow this structure:

```
[ID] <short title>
Type: feature | fix | refactor | infra | docs | security
Priority: P0 | P1 | P2
Scope: <paths/modules/services>
Problem: <what is wrong/missing>
Goal: <expected end-state>
Implementation Notes: <constraints, dependencies, UX/behavior>
Acceptance Criteria:
  - [ ] <testable condition 1>
  - [ ] <testable condition 2>
Validation:
  - unit: <required tests>
  - integration/e2e: <required checks>
Risk: low | medium | high
Rollback: <how to safely revert>
```

If entries are free-form, AI must normalize each one into this structure before coding.

